I think the problem with it is the setting. The idea of "anon adopts a homeless wolf girl" is a nice one, but setting it in a modern world where anon had every other option available to him takes a lot away from the story, and the fact that it just feels like a lazy reconstruction of Segregation era America, complete with all the racial allegories, definitely doesn't do it any favours. It's a protein that's folded the wrong way to do its job properly in a living cell, and the way it's folded makes other molecules of the same protein cling to it, fold up wrong in the same way, and drift away, to alter more and more of the proteins until the cell dies.

A prion is not a living thing. It can't die. It's just a protein that's bent the wrong way, that kills the cell it's in, then spreads to others.

Prions are proteins that are misfolded and clump together, causing degradation/tissue damage. They mainly accumulate across the nervous system (brain, spine, etc) and can essentially cause a normal brain to become damaged to the point it looks like swiss cheese. It's the cause of Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease in humans, Mad Cow disease in bovines, Chronic Wasting Disease in cervids and other such related diseases. The frightening thing about prions are that they can survive freezing for a long time, high heat temperatures and stick around in the environment for decades.
